{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2002 |Team=Washington State Cougars |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Pacific 10 Conference |ShortConference=Pac 10 |Division= |CoachRank= 10 |APRank= 10 |Record=10-3 |ConfRecord=7-1 |HeadCoach=[[Mike Price]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach=[[Bill Doba]] |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Martin Stadium]] |Champion=Pac-10 Co-Champions |BowlTourney= [[2003 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] vs. [[2002 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Oklahoma]] |BowlTourneyResult= L, 34-14 }} {{2002 Pacific-10 football standings}} The '''2002 Washington State Cougars football team''' represented [[Washington State University]] in the [[college football]] [[2002 NCAA Division I-A football season|season of 2002-2003]]. The team was led by fourteenth-year head coach [[Mike Price]], and played its home games at [[Martin Stadium]] in [[Pullman, Washington|Pullman]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]].
